<br>
Population growth in technologically advanced countries tend to slow, while the third world nations sky rocket... must be a condom thing.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=hamster>Hamster</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Space Tourist</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(8/14/02 8:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=92.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/16.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Could farming the asteroids feed the third world?</span><hr size=1> I don't know about agriculture but it might be possible at some point in the future for resource deprived countries to add wealth by asteroid mining.  I remember reading some articles where Nigeria thought about this possibility.  Doesn't seem very likely but then again it doesn't hurt to brainstorm.  To get back to agriculture, I think the main problem with mass agriculture in space is creating the life support infrastructure needed for the plants.  Building up large enough areas with the required energy and life support for crops to feed millions or billions of people could be a major hurdle. <br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/uzaphod4468.showPublicProfile?language=EN>zaphod4468</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ezOP</span><br>  Posts: 749<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(8/14/02 8:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=92.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.bbc.co.uk/cult/hitchhikers/gallery/images/100/zaphod2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/7.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Could farming the asteroids feed the third world?</span><hr size=1> Of course the ultimate solution would be a Dyson Sphere (yes that's Freeman Dyson)<br>
<br>
