<br>
An actual scenario would be an Earth where people don't want to see every marginal area farmed. Turning the Earth into a big food factory and recycling plant sounds very dull. An Earth where people don't wish to see the oceans covered in floating farms. Where the energy needed to power the lighting for underground farms cannot be obtained(possibly because ecowackies banned nuclear power).<br>
<br>
Human population doubles in just two generations. Even with innovative scientific progress to help out there will come a point in the not too distant future when we won't be able to produce enough food to feed ourselves. Unless we make laws to control population growth.   <br>
